Well, that really was some excellent bowling from England, especially in those last few overs when they just didn't give the batsmen anything much to hit. The early wickets set the tone and Australia could never quite get themselves back into rhythm. George Bailey made a half-century but fell trying to lift the rate. There wasn't a single six in the innings, which tells you something. The question is whether the drop-in pitch will prove to be as difficult for England's batsmen as it seemed at time for Australia. Join us in half an hour to see whether England can chase down 218 and finish this series with a second victory.
